reviews.review_text: First and last US shows As a Brit deadhead we used to only get a visit from the boys every ten years or so... Wembley 72, Ally Pally 74, Wembley 90 and so on. In 94' my wife and I made it over to the US for the first two nights at USAir and boy what a show this was. The pervious night we were both just stepped jet-lagged to death and we lost our hire car in the lot after the show (what colour was it...hell if I remember...we'd only picked it up 3 hours before at BWI). For this show we were slept, fed, watered and ready to groove. Highlights for me...the extended tease from Jerry as he moved from Help to Slipknot, but the whole of the second half is a dream with one of my favourite all time Stella Blues. Sadly these two nights was the first and last times I saw the Dead in the US before Jerry slipped over the line.
